=Description=

"The Openness Constituent Group focuses on the emergence and adoption of open technologies, practices, policies, and initiatives, and how they affect the delivery and support of education. Topics include but are not limited to free and open source software, open content, open educational resources, open courseware, open standards, and management practices such as open business and enterprise 2.0.

This group meets at the EDUCAUSE Annual Conference and uses the electronic discussion list to discuss issues throughout the year."
(http://www.educause.edu/groups/openness/130996?time=1230310559)


